column5: hi i will be staying at lake Wabigoon lake outfitters. just wondering what to expect for fishing. going to target walleyes, northerns and muskies. possibly some perch also. thanks

I guide occasionally at the camp, walleye are on the humps, lots of bigger pike being caught deep on the humps jigging walleye, weed areas always hold pike and musky. The weed bite for musky has been( in my opinion) slower than most years but plenty being caught still, try casting at rock structure too.
